  "prompt": "I am interested in a girl but she wants to just be friends. What do I do?",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear that you're going through this. Navigating feelings when they're not reciprocated can be challenging, but there are several steps you can take to handle the situation thoughtfully:\n\n1. **Acknowledge Your Feelings:**\n   - It's completely normal to feel disappointed, sad, or even frustrated when someone you care about sees you only as a friend. Give yourself permission to feel these emotions without judgment.\n\n2. **Respect Her Feelings:**\n   - It's important to honor her perspective and decision. Trying to push her into a romantic relationship when she isn't interested can strain or even damage the friendship.\n\n3. **Assess Your Friendship:**\n   - Reflect on whether you can maintain a platonic relationship without it causing you ongoing emotional discomfort. Sometimes, taking a step back can help you gain clarity and heal.\n\n4. **Focus on Self-Care:**\n   - Engage in activities that make you happy and help you grow. Whether it's pursuing hobbies, spending time with other friends, or focusing on personal goals, investing in yourself can boost your well-being.\n\n5. **Open Communication:**\n   - If it feels appropriate and you\u2019re comfortable, have an honest conversation with her about how you feel. Ensure it's a respectful dialogue where both of you can express your thoughts freely.\n\n6. **Explore Other Relationships:**\n   - When you're ready, meeting new people can open up opportunities for new connections. This doesn't diminish your current friendship but broadens your social circle.\n\n7. **Seek Support:**\n   - Talking to trusted friends, family members, or a counselor can provide additional perspectives and support as you navigate your feelings.\n\n8. **Give It Time:**\n   - Healing from unreciprocated feelings takes time. Be patient with yourself and understand that it's okay to seek distance if needed to move forward.\n\nRemember, it's admirable that you value her and are considering her feelings. Building a healthy friendship or eventually finding a relationship that reciprocates your feelings both deserve respect and care.",
